  "body": "\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nUsing 4.0.1 of Truffle, `truffle test` returns this error after compiling.\r\n```\r\nimport ether from './helpers/ether';\r\n^^^^^^\r\n\r\nSyntaxError: Unexpected token import\r\n    at createScript (vm.js:74:10)\r\n    at Object.runInThisContext (vm.js:116:10)\r\n    at Module._compile (module.js:537:28)\r\n    at Object.Module._extensions..js (module.js:584:10)\r\n    at Module.load (module.js:507:32)\r\n    at tryModuleLoad (module.js:470:12)\r\n    at Function.Module._load (module.js:462:3)\r\n    at Module.require (module.js:517:17)\r\n    at require (internal/module.js:11:18)\r\n    at /Users/brianedelman/.nvm/versions/node/v8.4.0/lib/node_modules/truffle/node_modules/mocha/lib/mocha.js:231:27\r\n```\r\nThis is the first import line in one of my js test files.\r\n\r\nI ran into this issue in the beta and added `require('babel-register')` to my truffle.js file. This fixes the import error and tests run.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nWith 4.0.1, run truffle test with new development network that is generated (or with old way). Make sure the test has an import statement at the top.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nAdding babel require seems to fix the issue.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: 10.12.6\r\n* Truffle version: 4.0.1\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* node version: 8.4.0\r\n* npm version: 5.5.1\r\n",
